        "verdict": "in-progress",
        "topFinding": "Yes& Cattery is a well-built, security-clean, feature-complete Phase 2 marketplace that is not yet carrying real money or real users, so its health is strong (79) and the verdict is in-progress rather than needs-attention. The theme that matters before launch gate 1 (verify release-to-payout end-to-end) is money-path robustness: four independent lenses converged on a Stripe webhook that records an event as processed and returns HTTP 200 before the DB write succeeds, so a transient failure strands a captured deposit as an unreserved order with no retry, no server-side log, and no admin visibility, while the orders table cascade-deletes financial records when a breeder deletes their cattery. None of this is a live bug today (Stripe is in test mode with demo data) but it is exactly what end-to-end payment verification will surface, and all of it is fixable now. No hard-rule breach exists: secrets are clean, RLS is comprehensive, and the screened-badge and buyer-privacy invariants hold.",
        "actionsOpen": 15,
        "actionsClosed": 0,
